{"word":"προεῖπον/προείρηκα","slug":"προεῖπον/προείρηκα","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>προεῖπον</el>/<el>προείρηϰα</el></b> [<el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:πρό\">πρό</a>, <a class=\"S\" href=\"S:εἶπον\">εἶπον</a></el>]<b><p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>1.</pp></b> ‘tell about <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ someth.\">someth.</a> before it happens’, <b>foretell, tell beforehand <a href='B:470 24:25'>Mt 24:25</a>; <a href='B:480 13:23'>Mk 13:23</a>; <a href='B:510 1:16'>Ac 1:16</a>; <a href='B:520 9:29'>Ro 9:29</a>; <a href='B:540 13:2'>2 Cor 13:2</a></b> (of past statement in tandem <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ w.\">w.</a> current statement expressed in <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:προλέγω\">προλέγω</a></el>); <b><a href='B:680 3:2'>2 Pt 3:2</a>; <a href='B:720 1:1'>Jd 17</a>.<p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>2.</pp></b> ‘express <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ someth.\">someth.</a> said before’, <b>say before/previously,</b> in oral presentation <b><a href='B:550 1:9'>Gal 1:9</a>; <a href='B:590 4:6'>1 Th 4:6</a>;</b> in an earlier part of a writing <b><a href='B:540 7:3'>2 Cor 7:3</a></b> (<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ s.\">s.</a> <a href='B:540 3:2'>3:2</a>; <a href='B:540 6:11'>6:11</a>); <b><a href='B:650 4:7'>Hb 4:7</a>; <a href='B:650 10:15'>10:15</a> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ v.l.\">v.l.</a></b> Also <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ s.\">s.</a> <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:προλέγω\">προλέγω</a></el>. <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:προεῖδον\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:προείρηκα\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}